{"lemma":"عَمِيقَةٍ","slug":"عَمِيقَةٍ","root":"ع.م.ق","root_slug":"ع-م-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-م-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَمِيق","root":"عمق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30560"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"deep","examples":[{"text":"الْبَحِيرَةُ عَمِيقَةٌ جِدًّا وَتَحْتَوِي عَلَى الْكَثِيرِ مِن الْأَسْمَاكِ الْجَمِيلَةِ.","english":"The lake is very deep and contains many beautiful fish."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb عَمُقَ (ʕamuqa, “to be deep”). Compare to Aramaic עַמִּיקָא (ʕammīqā)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.miːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30560","headword_ar":"عَمِيقٌ","root":"Emq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is of the dial. of the people of El-Hijáz: and the tribe of Temeem say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiyqN","text_ar":"مَعِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, TA.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biy^orN EamiyqapN","text_ar":"بِيْرٌ عَمِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiyqapN","text_ar":"مَعِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", formed by transposition, (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A deep well:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * Msb, K, * TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumuqN","text_ar":"عُمُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaqN","text_ar":"عِمَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamaAy^iqu","text_ar":"عَمَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaAqN","text_ar":"عِمَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  Also, applied to a [road such as is termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~","text_ar":"فَجّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) as in the Kur xxii. 28, (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Remote,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far-extending;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mujáhid, O, K;) and so as applied to a place; (Msb;) [so too ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiqN","text_ar":"عَمِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a desert, as in the verse cited above, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamoqN","text_ar":"عَمْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and, applied to a road,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiyqN","text_ar":"عَمِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more used than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiyqN","text_ar":"مَعِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiyqN","text_ar":"عَمِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~","text_ar":"فَجّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or, app., accord. to IAar, not thus when applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~","text_ar":"فَجّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning a road. (TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamoqN","text_ar":"عَمْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","Lth","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}